# native-host-instance.form

The host instance is the always-on native body shape for Mac, Windows, and
Android. A shell script, launchd plist, PowerShell wrapper, Android service,
ffmpeg process, Whisper process, driver, or OS API may carry resource access,
but none of those is the decision-maker.

The decision-maker is `form/form-stdlib/native-host-instance.fk`, now reachable
through the self-contained native `form-cli` command:

```text
native-host <platform> <mic> <camera> <screen> <speech_gate> <freq>
            <surprises> <samples> [message]
```

The result is a compact carrier row:

```text
native-host-instance|platform|native|listening|sharing|transcribing|
surprise-count|learned-count|decision|share-route
```

The native presence body in `form/native/presence/form_presence_host.c` supplies
an always-on tick (`FORM_PRESENCE_TICKS=0`) for hosts that need a persistent C
process, while Android packages the same C-bootstrapped `form-cli` as
`libform_cli_exec.so` and executes it from `nativeLibraryDir`. Those processes
measure and carry; `native-host-instance.fk` decides.

One instance breath composes the existing proven organs:

- `host-sense-organ.fk` reads which host resources are active and whether the
  host is streaming.
- `speech-organ.fk` decides when audio becomes trusted transcription.
- `surprise-salience.fk` decides which prediction errors matter.
- `co-learning-stream.fk` folds new samples into learned shape memory.
- `mesh-dispatch.fk` decides whether an incoming mesh message is a share/gold
  receipt or an ask to answer.

The receipt is:

```text
(native-host-instance platform native? listening? sharing? transcribing?
 surprise-count learned-count decision share-route)
```

The same recipe names `macos`, `windows`, and `android` as supported native host
platforms. Unsupported platforms are refused by the body, not by a wrapper.

Mac, Windows, and Android launch persistent native host processes that tick this
cell continuously, share typed receipts on the mesh, learn from their own
streams, and choose actions from Form readings. Shell/PowerShell/launchd and OS
services remain carriers for process supervision and hardware access; they are
not the decision boundary.

Proof: `form/form-stdlib/tests/native-host-instance-band.fk` returns `4095` and
is registered in `form/fourth-arm-bands.txt` for fkwu four-way validation.
`form/form-stdlib/tests/form-cli-band.fk` returns `1023`, proving the native-host
verb and dispatch row across Go/Rust/TS/fkwu before it is packaged for a host.
